<aside class="reading-list">
<div class="header column">
<div class="truthout-logo">
<img width="200" height="200" src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-200x200.png" class="truthout-logo" alt="A white lower-case t on a black background" srcset="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-200x200.png 200w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-400x400.png 400w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-250x250.png 250w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-270x270.png 270w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-192x192.png 192w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-180x180.png 180w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148-32x32.png 32w, https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/cropped-Truthout-T-logo-sq-1200x1200-e1521532408148.png 512w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" />
</div>
<span class="meta-label uppercase">Reading List</span>
</div>
<div class="column entry-content">
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #cc822e;'>Prisons &amp; Policing</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/as-coronavirus-spreads-through-prisons-states-are-failing-incarcerated-people/">As Coronavirus Spreads Through Prisons, States Are Failing Incarcerated People</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #1958aa;'>Politics &amp; Elections</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/portlands-rental-crisis-created-an-opening-for-democratic-socialist-candidates/">Portland’s Rental Crisis Created an Opening for Democratic Socialist Candidates</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/covid-19-exposes-the-delicate-economic-balance-we-all-live-in-under-capitalism/">COVID-19 Exposes the Delicate Economic Balance We All Live in Under Capitalism</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/ilhan-omar-bill-would-cancel-rent-and-mortgage-payments-for-duration-of-pandemic/">Ilhan Omar Bill Would Cancel Rent and Mortgage Payments for Duration of Pandemic</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #1958aa;'>Politics &amp; Elections</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/attorney-general-barr-refuses-to-release-9-11-documents-to-victims-families/">Attorney General Barr Refuses to Release 9/11 Documents to Victims&#8217; Families</a>
</article>
<article class="reading-list-item">
<div class='sections' style='color: #2c5b53;'>Economy &amp; Labor</div>
<a href="https://truthout.org/articles/postal-workers-union-leader-warns-the-usps-could-be-dead-in-three-months/">Postal Workers Union Leader Warns the USPS Could Be Dead in Three Months</a>
</article>
</div>
</aside>
</div>
<div class="entry-content primary-content-column columns small-12 medium-8">
<p>Louisiana faces one of the worst outbreaks of the coronavirus in the United States. New data shows Black people account for 70% of all the state&rsquo;s coronavirus deaths, though they comprise just 32% of the state&rsquo;s population. Louisiana also has the highest incarceration rate in the country, and more than 65% of the people in its jails and prisons are Black. At least 28 people are infected, and 22 corrections staff have tested positive. State corrections officials are sending infected prisoners to the Louisiana State Penitentiary &mdash; known as Angola, the largest maximum-security prison in the United States &mdash; where they are being held in Camp J, a notorious part of the prison that was shut down in 2018 because of inhumane treatment. &#8232;The <span class="caps">ACLU</span> of Louisiana sued to stop the statewide transfer of <span class="caps">COVID</span>-19 patients to Angola prison, but a judge denied the request last Thursday. We speak with Alanah Odoms Hebert, executive director of the <span class="caps">ACLU</span> of Louisiana, and Albert Woodfox, who served the longest time in solitary confinement of any prisoner in the United States &mdash; 44 years in Angola prison. His memoir is <em>Solitary: Unbroken by Four Decades in Solitary Confinement. My Story of Transformation and Hope</em>.</p>
<h2>TRANSCRIPT<em><br></em></h2>
<div class="text">
<p><strong><span class="caps">AMY</span> <span class="caps">GOODMAN</span>:</strong> This is <em>Democracy Now!</em>, democracynow.org, <em>The War and Peace Report</em>. I&rsquo;m Amy Goodman, broadcasting from the epicenter of the coronavirus pandemic in the United States, New York City, with Juan Gonz&aacute;lez, who is in New Jersey, the second-most afflicted state.</p>
<p>But we&rsquo;re turning now to Louisiana, which is facing one of the worst outbreaks of the coronavirus. New data shows African Americans account for 70% of all Louisiana&rsquo;s coronavirus deaths, even as they are just 32% of the Louisiana&rsquo;s population. Louisiana also has the highest incarceration rate in the United States. More than 65% of the people in its jails and prisons are Black. At least 28 people are infected, and 22 corrections staff have tested positive.</p>
<p>State correction officials are sending infected prisoners to Louisiana State Penitentiary, known as Angola, the largest maximum-security prison in the United States, holding them in Camp J, a notorious building that was shut down in 2018 because of inhumane treatment of the men held there. Officials have confirmed there are no ventilators at Camp J. The <span class="caps">ACLU</span> of Louisiana sued to stop the statewide transfer of <span class="caps">COVID</span>-19 patients to Angola prison, but the judge denied the request last Thursday.</p><div class="truth-post-content-high  inline-callout-container" id="truth-255792"><aside class=" callout inline-callout callout--subscribe callout--dark" id="truth-255397">
